<div class="page">

  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">About Discerna</div>
    <h1 class="hero-heading">Built by a teacher,<br>for <em>every</em> teacher</h1>
    <p class="hero-lead">Discerna started with a staffroom conversation and a problem every teacher knows — how do you give every student genuinely individual feedback, when you have 28 of them?</p>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <div class="story">
    <p>I've been teaching across NSW and Victoria for seven years. One of the things I've always found genuinely difficult isn't assessing writing — it's finding the time and the words to give each student feedback that actually means something to them specifically. Not a generic comment. Not a rubber stamp. Something that sees <strong>their</strong> piece of writing and tells them exactly where they are and where to go next.</p>

    <p>The conversation that sparked Discerna happened with a group of colleagues who were feeling the same pressure. We were talking about how to make feedback more individual without it taking over our lives. We knew AI could help — but we wanted something built around the way Australian teachers actually think and work, against the curricula we actually teach.</p>

    <p>So I built it. Discerna is not here to replace your professional judgement. You know your students. You know the context behind a piece of writing — whether it was written under pressure, whether English is an additional language, whether a child had a difficult morning. Discerna doesn't know any of that unless you tell it.</p>

    <p>What it can do is give you a <strong>second set of expert eyes</strong> — a detailed, curriculum-aligned starting point that you can agree with, push back on, or use as a springboard. It's designed to make you feel more confident in your assessment, not to do your job for you.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="pull-quote">
    <p>"Discerna is not here to replace your professional judgement. It's here to make you feel more confident in it."</p>
    <div class="pull-quote-attr">— The teacher who built this</div>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <div class="how-title">How it works</div>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div>
        <div class="step-title">Upload or type de-identified student writing</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Photo, PDF, camera capture, or typed text. Remove student names before submitting — Discerna is designed for de-identified work only.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div>
        <div class="step-title">Choose the curriculum, year level and writing type</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Discerna supports all eight Australian states and territories, Foundation through Year 10, across VIC, NSW and AC v9.0 curriculums.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div>
        <div class="step-title">Receive a curriculum-aligned assessment</div>
        <div class="step-desc">An achievement level, a commendation drawn from the student's actual writing, three targeted goals for their next piece, and curriculum outcome codes.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <div>
        <div class="step-title">Use it, adapt it, make it yours</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Print it, save it to your session, or use it as a starting point for your own feedback. The assessment belongs to you — Discerna stores nothing.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="privacy-card">
    <div class="privacy-card-title">🔒 Privacy — what happens to student writing</div>
    <ul class="privacy-list">
      <li>Student writing is sent to Anthropic's API for assessment only — it is never stored, retained or used to train AI models.</li>
      <li>No student names, school names or identifying information should ever be submitted. Discerna reminds you of this before every assessment.</li>
      <li>For typed or pasted text, and for transcribed handwriting, Discerna applies a basic name scrubber as an additional safeguard — automatically removing common name patterns before submission. This is not a substitute for de-identifying writing before you submit.</li>
      <li>No accounts, no login, no persistent storage of any kind. When you close the tab, everything is gone.</li>
      <li>Discerna is designed for de-identified work. It is your responsibility as the teacher to ensure no personal information is included before submitting.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="cta">
    <a href="index.html" class="btn-primary">✦ Start assessing writing</a>
    <div class="cta-sub">Free to use · No account required · Built for Australian teachers</div>
  </div>

</div>

